songs.title: Five O’Clock Angel
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Every morning of every day
I wake up; it is the same ole thing
Fight the traffic, punch the clock
Concrete floors wearing out my shoes
Tired of feeling the way I do
Three more trucks to load, it never stops
They are killing me from nine to five
When it is quitting time, I come alive

[Chorus]
Because I got a woman
Who holds me in her arms and understands
A beautiful woman
Who knows how hard it is to be a man
No telling where I would be right now
If she had not been sent down
So I do not have to face this world all by myself
She is my five o'clock angel

[Verse 2]
Like a branded man down where I work
The company name sewn on my shirt
They can buy my time, but they do not own me
There is more to me than what I do
I have got feelings too
There somewhere else I would rather be
You can have your beer and whiskey sour
I do not need no Happy Hour

[Chorus]

[Outro]
No telling where I would be right now
If she had not been sent down
So I do not have to face this world all by myself
She is my five o'clock angel
My five o'clock angel
